oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Andrews Tabernacle Christian Methodist Episicopal Church

Color photograph of a church with white, wooden siding. The three bay south elevation features two one-over-one sash windows painted blue. The front (east) facade has a small gabled porch with a double leafed doorway. the church has a stone foundation and a corrugated tin gabled roof. Concrete steps and two iron handrails lead to the front entryway. A cornerstone is located at the bottom left of the front facade.
Andrews Tabernacle Christian Methodist Episcopal Church was established in 1897.
